Meanwhile, Trump encourages violence against journalists with his constant attacks on the press. He is sending a message to authoritarian leaders across the world that America will no longer stand up for our core freedoms.

Why hasn’t the U.S. acted? I asked the FBI to open an investigation in July. They replied with a form letter that didn’t say whether they would. I hope the FBI is committed to getting to the bottom of the murder of a Virginia resident.

One year after the Saudi government killed Jamal Khashoggi for exposing its human rights abuses, President Trump has failed to hold Saudi Arabia accountable and has undermined the very freedom of the press Jamal stood for.

Two years ago in Las Vegas, 58 people were killed and hundreds more injured. Today in Washington, we’re not doing anything about it. That’s unacceptable. The Senate must vote on legislation to curb the gun violence plaguing our country. We don’t have to live—or die—like this.
